-- China's Country Garden forecasts better H2 for property sector
-- 
-- Tue Aug 19, 2014 05:01AM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, Aug 19 (Reuters) - Chinese developer Country Garden Holdings Co Ltd <2007.HK> said on Tuesday it expects the mainland property sector in the second half of this year to outperform the first six months.

Country Garden president Mo Bin was speaking at an earnings press conference after the company reported a 26 percent rise in first-half net profit.